{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17493255","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17493255"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T07:02:44+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T07:02:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1268"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1268","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1268"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.07,0.76,0.03,0.14,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1268"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"30545"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1268","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1268"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1268"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"16487"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"3542"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1064"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1372"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13451"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42269"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"30545","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/30545"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 25-year-old woman presents with a painful, swollen neck over the past week that is getting worse. She also reports new onset sleeplessness and a sensation of anxiety and restlessness. Apart from a recent sore throat and dry cough, which she did not see her GP for, she has been otherwise well.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EShe has no known medical conditions. She takes the oral contraceptive pill as a form of contraception. She has no allergies and no family history of medical conditions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she is afebrile at 36.5C, her blood pressure is 110/85 mmHg and she has a heart rate of 100/min with a regular pulse. A fine tremor is noted on extension of both her hands and placing a piece of paper on top. She has diffuse tenderness and warmth over the lateral lobes of her thyroid gland. Pemberton\u0027s sign is negative and there is no exophthalmos or lid lag of her eyes.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely cause of her presentation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hashimoto\u0027s disease","Subacute thyroiditis","Drug-induced thyroiditis","Graves\u0027 disease","Trauma"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe presentation described fits with a likely diagnosis of \u003Cstrong\u003Esubacute\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003Ethyroiditis\u003C/strong\u003E. This condition is an acute inflammatory condition caused by a recent viral illness, in this case likely an upper respiratory infection (indicated by her recent cough and sore throat). The condition follows a general course of hyperthyroidism, which is likely what is causing this woman\u0027s current symptoms and signs (fine tremor and relative tachycardia for a young woman). Sometimes it can then turn into a period of hypothyroidism.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA characteristic feature of this condition is a sudden tender and swollen thyroid gland, which is uncommon in other causes of hyperthyroidism, such as Grave\u0027s disease. The diagnosis is made on clinical grounds and supported by thyroid tests consistent with primary hyperthyroidism (high T4 and low TSH).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGraves disease is a decent differential diagnosis, but this often occurs over a longer period of time and can be commonly seen with eye signs as well.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere are no reports of trauma to suggest this as being a cause for her symptoms, the OCP is not known to result in hyperthyroidism, unlike other medications such as amiodarone, of which she is not on hence suggesting a drug-induced cause being unlikely. Hashimoto\u0027s is a condition of hypothyroidism, which is not consistent with her symptoms and signs.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Subacute thyroiditis results in hyperthyroidism after a viral illness"],"references":["Hershman, 2020. Subacute thyroiditis [online]. MSD Manual. Accessed at: https://www.msdmanuals.com/professional/endocrine-and-metabolic-disorders/thyroid-disorders/subacute-thyroiditis."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"16487"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1268"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"16487","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/16487"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2022-12-02T08:04:20+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-08-02T22:40:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1268"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"30545"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"update